  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "This non-essentialist perspective acknowledges that the identity and functionality of a system are co-constructed through its ongoing interactions with the environment.",
    "The system remains distinct yet interdependent, constantly redefining its boundaries and properties in response to external stimuli.",
    "This dynamic and relational understanding of entities as autopoietic systems contrasts sharply with the essentialist view, which treats entities as having a fixed essence that exists independently of their surroundings.",
    "Autopoiesis provides a generalized ontological perspective that facilitates critique of social systems, cognition (psychic systems), action and materiality as autopoietic systems or distinctions (see Luhmann 2013).",
    "While any system can be observed as an autopoietic system-environment distinction, the internal structure of a system involves the differentiation of distinctions within the distinction of the system itself and operating under the principle of autopoiesis."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}